88
00:06:21.643 --> 00:06:22.518
Please.

89
00:06:23.643 --> 00:06:25.476
-We have a problem.
-What is it?


90
00:06:26.101 --> 00:06:28.560
It seems a fly fell in his drink.

91
00:06:28.643 --> 00:06:30.101
Excuse me.

92
00:06:30.185 --> 00:06:32.560
-Let's avoid further embarrassment.
-Yes.


93
00:06:32.643 --> 00:06:34.935
The hot chocolate is on the house.

94
00:06:35.018 --> 00:06:36.310
The hot chocolate?

95
00:06:38.351 --> 00:06:41.393
Just the hot chocolate
is on the house. Funny!


96
00:06:41.476 --> 00:06:43.018
What about the rest?

97
00:06:43.101 --> 00:06:46.185
The rest is the whole menu.
You ate it all.


98
00:06:46.268 --> 00:06:47.351
Even a fly!

99
00:06:47.435 --> 00:06:50.101
Ladies and gentlemen, a minute, please.

100
00:06:50.185 --> 00:06:51.310
Pay attention.

101
00:06:51.393 --> 00:06:53.018
Pay attention, silly girl.

102
00:06:53.101 --> 00:06:56.101
I'm sorry for disturbing your breakfast,

103
00:06:56.185 --> 00:06:59.851
but, unfortunately,
we're served flies in Brazil.


104
00:06:59.935 --> 00:07:04.143
You can't leave without paying
after eating everything on the menu.


105
00:07:04.226 --> 00:07:08.143
I will pay for it. That's not the point.
It will cost you a lot.


106
00:07:08.226 --> 00:07:11.185
I'll pay.
I don't need charity or anything.


107
00:07:11.268 --> 00:07:15.393
-I want justice.
-Clean it up, please.


108
00:07:15.476 --> 00:07:19.185
Don't touch the crime scene! All right?

109
00:07:19.268 --> 00:07:22.018
I want a forensic examination. I'll do it.

110
00:07:26.101 --> 00:07:29.560
Guys, I just can't. 
It's sad, you know?

111
00:07:29.643 --> 00:07:33.518
It died on such a beautiful morning.
Did you see that?


112
00:07:34.101 --> 00:07:35.560
It used to fly so freely.

113
00:07:35.643 --> 00:07:38.185
What a sudden and unnecessary death!

114
00:07:39.393 --> 00:07:43.185
I killed it, lady!
I killed it. I'm devastated!


115
00:07:44.393 --> 00:07:45.560
Poor thing!

116
00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:48.268
Forgive me, Buddha!

117
00:07:48.351 --> 00:07:51.476
All right, no harm done.
No need to pay for anything.


118
00:07:51.560 --> 00:07:53.226
It's on the house, okay?

119
00:07:54.185 --> 00:07:55.351
You can leave now.

120
00:07:55.435 --> 00:07:59.060
That's great.
Let's avoid further embarrassment.


121
00:07:59.143 --> 00:08:00.685
-Sure.
-I'll forgive you.


122
00:08:03.518 --> 00:08:04.810
<i>I'm not ashamed.</i>

123
00:08:04.893 --> 00:08:07.310
<i>People screw us over all the time.</i>

124
00:08:07.393 --> 00:08:09.893
<i>Why should I pay a
lot of money to eat?</i>

125
00:08:14.351 --> 00:08:17.226
<i>One scam after another has led me here,</i>

126
00:08:17.726 --> 00:08:20.226
<i>to the most important day of my life.</i>

127
00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:25.935
Listen, this is the last time
I'm helping you with your scams. I'm done.


128
00:08:26.435 --> 00:08:27.435
Great.

129
00:08:28.060 --> 00:08:31.143
Today is my last day. I'm done with you.

130
00:08:31.226 --> 00:08:32.685
You always say that.

131
00:08:32.768 --> 00:08:35.310
Then, a week later,
you ask me for a favor.


132
00:08:35.393 --> 00:08:36.518
I know you, Clóvis.

133
00:08:36.601 --> 00:08:38.393
I sold Christ, man.

134
00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:40.060
What?

135
00:08:40.143 --> 00:08:41.768
<i>Christ the Redeemer.</i>

136
00:08:41.851 --> 00:08:42.935
You're lying!

137
00:08:43.018 --> 00:08:45.726
Who's going to buy that statue?

138
00:08:46.268 --> 00:08:49.976
A crook, someone who wants
to benefit from the crisis.


139
00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:54.435
I did Brazil a favor by taking money
from a corrupt businessman.


140
00:08:54.518 --> 00:08:56.268
Come on, Robin Hood.

141
00:08:56.351 --> 00:08:59.435
I'll say more.
You don't have the guts to do that.


142
00:08:59.518 --> 00:09:01.893
I'll show you. 
I have the documents.

143
00:09:02.393 --> 00:09:04.685
I dare you to say this is fake.

144
00:09:05.268 --> 00:09:08.976
I even created a website
with a code so they can check it.


145
00:09:09.060 --> 00:09:10.685
It's all there.

146
00:09:10.768 --> 00:09:12.310
Have you no shame?

147
00:09:12.393 --> 00:09:13.643
No, none at all.

148
00:09:14.143 --> 00:09:18.226
I told them it is confidential
under the state secrecy law.


149
00:09:18.310 --> 00:09:22.185
I said the government
won't disclose it yet to avoid protests,


150
00:09:22.268 --> 00:09:25.560
and the press is being paid, but will
denounce it later to play innocent.


151
00:09:25.643 --> 00:09:29.060
I asked for a bribe
for the mayor, for myself,


152
00:09:29.143 --> 00:09:31.393
for the governor and for myself again,

153
00:09:31.476 --> 00:09:33.560
so I can set
him up with the deal.

154
00:09:33.643 --> 00:09:35.560
-Did they buy it?
-Of course.


155
00:09:35.643 --> 00:09:38.435
You can't trust a deal without bribery.

156
00:09:39.060 --> 00:09:40.810
<i>A hundred years ago in Paris,</i>

157
00:09:40.893 --> 00:09:46.393
<i>a man tried to sell the Eiffel Tower</i>
<i>to one of the biggest scrap metal dealers.</i>


158
00:09:46.476 --> 00:09:47.935
<i>He was so successful</i>

159
00:09:48.018 --> 00:09:50.976
<i>that he went back to France</i>
<i>and sold it again.</i>


160
00:09:51.476 --> 00:09:54.268
<i>We are used to copying things from abroad.</i>

161
00:09:54.351 --> 00:09:57.726
<i>The Christ statue</i>
<i>was left unattended, so I sold it.</i>


162
00:09:58.226 --> 00:09:59.060
<i>I did.</i>

163
00:09:59.143 --> 00:10:00.060
SOLD

164
00:10:00.143 --> 00:10:04.143
<i>All I needed was</i>
<i>a corrupt man willing to make a deal.</i>


165
00:10:04.226 --> 00:10:06.185
<i>And there are many like</i> <i>him here.</i>

166
00:10:06.268 --> 00:10:07.393
Where is the money?

167
00:10:08.018 --> 00:10:12.060
-Now? In broad daylight?
-Don't worry. It's all good.


168
00:10:12.143 --> 00:10:16.018
People don't hide things anymore.
The more explicit, the better.


169
00:10:16.101 --> 00:10:17.685
Everything is for sale.

170
00:10:17.768 --> 00:10:20.518
The Amazon is no longer ours.

171
00:10:20.601 --> 00:10:23.101
Not even a cricket
speaks Portuguese there.


172
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:25.685
Where is the money?

173
00:10:28.435 --> 00:10:30.101
Why are you hiding it?

174
00:10:30.185 --> 00:10:32.268
Give me that. Don't be suspicious.

175
00:10:32.351 --> 00:10:36.435
I loved this vase.
I'll take it. Don't mind me. Bye.


176
00:10:36.518 --> 00:10:39.185
<i>I have the solution for our people</i>

177
00:10:39.935 --> 00:10:42.726
<i>A good business like this</i>
<i>No one's ever seen</i>


178
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:46.435
<i>Everything is ready</i>
<i>Just come and take it</i>


179
00:10:46.518 --> 00:10:50.018
<i>The solution is putting Brazil up for rent</i>

180
00:10:50.101 --> 00:10:52.310
<i>We won't pay for anything</i>…

181
00:10:53.351 --> 00:10:55.851
<i>This country is a joke.</i>
<i>Why should I be serious?</i>


182
00:10:56.768 --> 00:10:58.810
<i>Come on, it was a good scam.</i>

183
00:11:03.726 --> 00:11:07.351
-You pulled it off!
-Yes! Thanks for the recognition.


184
00:11:07.435 --> 00:11:11.268
<i>Not to brag, but I totally rocked it.</i>

185
00:11:11.768 --> 00:11:14.435
<i>The foreigners will love it</i>

186
00:11:15.018 --> 00:11:17.310
<i>It's got the Atlantic and a sea view</i>…

187
00:11:17.893 --> 00:11:20.851
<i>After everything I went through,</i>
<i>all the trouble,</i>


188
00:11:20.935 --> 00:11:22.976
<i>I worked so hard,</i>

189
00:11:23.060 --> 00:11:25.685
<i>and I was living</i>
<i>the best moment of my life.</i>


190
00:11:25.768 --> 00:11:27.560
<i>We won't pay for anything</i>

191
00:11:28.560 --> 00:11:30.351
<i>We won't pay for anything</i>

192
00:11:31.226 --> 00:11:32.143
<i>It's all free</i>

193
00:11:32.226 --> 00:11:34.018
<i>It's time</i>

194
00:11:38.060 --> 00:11:40.518
<i>But since poor people</i>
<i>can't be happy for long,</i>


195
00:11:40.601 --> 00:11:42.185
<i>everything changed.</i>

196
00:11:44.768 --> 00:11:45.643
Clóvis.

197
00:11:46.435 --> 00:11:47.351
Is your TV on?

198
00:11:47.935 --> 00:11:48.810
Probably not.

199
00:11:49.310 --> 00:11:51.226
Turn on the news. 
We're screwed.

200
00:11:51.310 --> 00:11:53.018
It was at this cafe

201
00:11:53.101 --> 00:11:56.643
that the businessmen allegedly met a man

202
00:11:56.726 --> 00:11:58.893
who sold them Rio's <i>Christ the Redeemer</i>

203
00:11:59.601 --> 00:12:01.935
<i>under the false name of Lívio Romero.</i>

204
00:12:02.018 --> 00:12:04.851
<i>As you can see,</i>
<i>this is the sketch of the suspect.</i>


205
00:12:04.935 --> 00:12:09.143
For fuck's sake, man!

206
00:12:10.060 --> 00:12:12.601
Hey, big guy! I need my car!

207
00:12:13.226 --> 00:12:16.851
<i>I'm sorry, Tavinho, but I need that car.</i>

208
00:12:26.976 --> 00:12:29.935
-Clóvis!
-I paid for it! You are my accomplice!


209
00:12:30.018 --> 00:12:32.935
-What? Come on, Clóvis!
-Accomplice! That's right!


210
00:12:33.018 --> 00:12:35.518
<i>Now I'll get my money
and get out of here.</i>

211
00:12:45.310 --> 00:12:48.810
<i>However, the Senator</i>
<i>was faster than me and the cops.</i>


212
00:12:49.643 --> 00:12:52.101
<i>It's my fault for messing with them.</i>

213
00:12:52.601 --> 00:12:56.435
JUST GO AND BE HAPPY, SON
ART DOESN'T PAY


