What a hot place!

241
00:14:44.060 --> 00:14:45.476
NASA should study it,

242
00:14:45.560 --> 00:14:49.476
because I think
the sun is closer to here, for sure.


243
00:14:50.268 --> 00:14:52.518
I could fry a burger on the street.

244
00:14:52.601 --> 00:14:54.726
I don't do it. 
I have ethics.

245
00:14:56.518 --> 00:14:59.226
<i>But ethics is a complicated subject.</i>

246
00:14:59.310 --> 00:15:02.060
-Good afternoon. All good here?
-Hi!


247
00:15:02.685 --> 00:15:04.435
Distinguished customers.

248
00:15:04.518 --> 00:15:08.476
I have Cheese-Lohane, Lohane-salad,
Chicken-Lohane and Lohane Light.


249
00:15:08.560 --> 00:15:10.310
I hope you speak English.

250
00:15:10.976 --> 00:15:14.601
-What are you having?
-The trailer's business license.


251
00:15:16.685 --> 00:15:19.060
Well, this one…

252
00:15:19.143 --> 00:15:21.518
It's not on the menu. 
We're short on it.

253
00:15:22.101 --> 00:15:26.143
You can't sell food without it.
I have to confiscate the trailer.


254
00:15:26.226 --> 00:15:27.060
No, sir.

255
00:15:27.601 --> 00:15:31.018
Please, don't. That's my business.

256
00:15:31.101 --> 00:15:32.935
You'll destroy my life.

257
00:15:33.018 --> 00:15:34.726
Please, help me out!

258
00:15:34.810 --> 00:15:38.560
Maybe, with some incentive…

259
00:15:39.268 --> 00:15:40.101
Get it?

260
00:15:42.060 --> 00:15:44.476
-A sweetener?
-Yes.


261
00:15:44.560 --> 00:15:45.851
A kickback, you know?

262
00:15:45.935 --> 00:15:48.143
To help me feed my children.

263
00:15:48.685 --> 00:15:49.518
I know.

264
00:15:50.018 --> 00:15:51.560
It's not sweet at all.

265
00:15:54.143 --> 00:15:55.810
Here. That's all I have.

266
00:15:59.393 --> 00:16:03.768
Well, it's not enough for me
and my friend Pantoja over there.


267
00:16:05.185 --> 00:16:06.310
So?

268
00:16:06.393 --> 00:16:07.935
I will…

269
00:16:08.893 --> 00:16:09.976
I'll look for more.

270
00:16:18.768 --> 00:16:20.060
This month's income.

271
00:16:20.643 --> 00:16:22.101
Now we're talking.

272
00:16:22.185 --> 00:16:23.268
Very sweet.

273
00:16:23.893 --> 00:16:24.935
Have a nice day.

274
00:16:25.643 --> 00:16:27.060
Let's go, Pantoja.

275
00:16:28.310 --> 00:16:29.393
What was that?

276
00:16:29.935 --> 00:16:31.393
<i>What a situation!</i>

277
00:16:32.310 --> 00:16:36.768
<i>I need a license, but it costs money,</i>
<i>so I need to work for it.</i>


278
00:16:36.851 --> 00:16:37.935
<i>It's crazy!</i>

279
00:16:38.476 --> 00:16:41.143
<i>I paid them, but
I didn't lose my trailer.</i>

280
00:16:42.435 --> 00:16:44.518
<i>But poor people can't be happy for long,</i>

281
00:16:44.601 --> 00:16:46.101
<i>so everything changed.</i>

282
00:16:46.185 --> 00:16:48.810
Don't do that! 
I'm begging you!

283
00:16:48.893 --> 00:16:50.351
This trailer is my life!

284
00:16:50.435 --> 00:16:52.893
-Don't take it away!
-Calm down, ma'am.


285
00:16:52.976 --> 00:16:56.518
You're not allowed to sell food here,
we have to take it away.


286
00:16:56.601 --> 00:16:58.518
Yes! I mean, no!

287
00:16:58.601 --> 00:17:00.143
Is it a yes or a no?

288
00:17:00.226 --> 00:17:04.476
Yes, I don't have a license,
but you can't take my trailer away.


289
00:17:04.560 --> 00:17:07.976
I already sorted it out
with your friend who came by.


290
00:17:09.268 --> 00:17:10.101
-Friend?
-Yes!


291
00:17:10.185 --> 00:17:13.226
-I have no friends. What about you?
-No friends.


292
00:17:21.476 --> 00:17:23.018
Fake inspectors?

293
00:17:23.101 --> 00:17:25.601
Yes, there are a lot of them.

294
00:17:25.685 --> 00:17:28.310
They take money from people like you.

295
00:17:28.393 --> 00:17:31.726
-You're a victim.
-Not exactly a victim, actually.


296
00:17:31.810 --> 00:17:35.351
If you hadn't paid them,
they would've gone away.


297
00:17:35.435 --> 00:17:38.976
-But you'll take it?
-Yes, but you'd still have your money.


298
00:17:39.060 --> 00:17:40.060
Let's go, Santos.

299
00:17:43.060 --> 00:17:45.685
<i>Alone, with no trailer and no money.</i>

300
00:17:46.601 --> 00:17:47.851
<i>I had nothing left.</i>

301
00:17:50.851 --> 00:17:51.810
<i>I mean…</i>

302
00:17:52.643 --> 00:17:53.851
<i>almost nothing.</i>

303
00:17:59.851 --> 00:18:01.101
<i>I needed to go to Rio.</i>

304
00:18:01.685 --> 00:18:03.226
I'm going to Rio, Jerusa!

305
00:18:03.310 --> 00:18:06.310
<i>In search of the only person</i>
<i>who could help me,</i>


306
00:18:06.393 --> 00:18:07.310
<i>my brother.</i>

307
00:18:10.310 --> 00:18:14.060
<i>He's always been discreet,</i>
<i>but I thought he'd done well in life,</i>


308
00:18:14.601 --> 00:18:16.518
<i>that he'd made it in a big city.</i>

309
00:18:17.310 --> 00:18:18.851
<i>He was doing better than me.</i>

310
00:18:21.185 --> 00:18:24.435
For fuck's sake!

311
00:18:24.518 --> 00:18:25.560
Did I kill you?

312
00:18:29.268 --> 00:18:30.101
Lohane?

313
00:18:30.185 --> 00:18:31.393
Clóvis!

314
00:18:31.476 --> 00:18:33.185
Did you have to show up now?

315
00:18:35.768 --> 00:18:37.851
Wait! Clóvis!

316
00:18:39.685 --> 00:18:41.560
Thank you, Lord!

317
00:18:42.351 --> 00:18:44.226
Clóvis!

318
00:18:48.518 --> 00:18:51.726
Why are you in such a hurry?
You didn't give me a kiss.


319
00:18:53.101 --> 00:18:53.935
Are you late?

320
00:18:54.935 --> 00:18:58.226
Focusing on traffic to avoid answering me.

321
00:18:59.310 --> 00:19:01.851
Talk to the driver only when necessary.

322
00:19:06.935 --> 00:19:08.060
Are you going away?

323
00:19:09.893 --> 00:19:13.018
You don't need to answer.
I don't wanna know.


324
00:19:16.393 --> 00:19:18.518
I thought you had a nicer car.

325
00:19:18.601 --> 00:19:20.518
I'm not judging you or anything.

326
00:19:21.601 --> 00:19:25.018
It's just that we always think
other people are doing well.


327
00:19:25.101 --> 00:19:28.851
I'm not saying you're not.
You're doing better than me.


328
00:19:28.935 --> 00:19:32.226
-But worse than I thought.
-Can't you see I'm focused?


329
00:19:32.310 --> 00:19:33.976
I'm sorry. Relax.

330
00:19:34.060 --> 00:19:36.351
You look like Wesley Safadão.

331
00:19:36.976 --> 00:19:39.476
Because of the hair, I guess.

332
00:19:39.560 --> 00:19:43.226
Your nickname in school
was Clóvis Bornay, remember?


333
00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:47.768
By the way, where are we going?

334
00:19:49.226 --> 00:19:51.393
Can you talk now? 
I need to talk.

335
00:19:51.476 --> 00:19:52.310
No.

336
00:19:57.851 --> 00:20:01.893
We've been driving for hours.
Where are you taking me? I'm curious.


337
00:20:02.476 --> 00:20:04.976
LAKES REGION

338
00:20:05.560 --> 00:20:07.685
This could be considered kidnapping.

339
00:20:09.518 --> 00:20:11.726
Yes, we've been driving for hours.

340
00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:13.768
No, this is not a kidnapping.

341
00:20:13.851 --> 00:20:17.518
I didn't take you against your will.
You entered my car.


342
00:20:17.601 --> 00:20:18.935
Get out, please.

343
00:20:19.685 --> 00:20:22.560
-You're so rude!
-I'm not rude.


344
00:20:22.643 --> 00:20:24.726
I said "please." Get out, please.

345
00:20:25.226 --> 00:20:27.768
-You haven't seen me in ages!
-Get out.


346
00:20:28.810 --> 00:20:31.810
-Clóvis, I need your help.
-Get out!


347
00:20:31.893 --> 00:20:34.310
-I'm in trouble!
-And you think I'm not?


348
00:20:34.393 --> 00:20:36.060
I'm in deep shit, dear.

349
00:20:36.143 --> 00:20:37.726
I'm up to my neck in shit.

350
00:20:37.810 --> 00:20:38.935
Not as bad as me.

351
00:20:39.018 --> 00:20:42.101
-I'm in trouble with the cops!
-Not interested. Move.


352
00:20:43.060 --> 00:20:45.810
Listen up, Clóvis. I have a trailer.

353
00:20:45.893 --> 00:20:49.601
I had one, but the cops confiscated it
for not having a license.


354
00:20:49.685 --> 00:20:54.351
Before that there was another raid,
and I bribed them, but they were fake!


355
00:20:54.435 --> 00:20:57.226
Now I have no money and no trailer!

356
00:20:57.310 --> 00:20:59.643
I have no other
way to make a living.

357
00:21:00.143 --> 00:21:04.310
Then I thought my brother could help me.
I'll pay you back.


358
00:21:04.393 --> 00:21:06.685
I have no money. 
How could I help you?

359
00:21:10.935 --> 00:21:11.810
I understand.

360
00:21:12.851 --> 00:21:14.185
Crooks are everywhere.

361
00:21:14.851 --> 00:21:17.601
You might not believe me,
but I can prove it.


362
00:21:17.685 --> 00:21:18.768
I'll show you.

363
00:21:28.601 --> 00:21:29.935
You're a criminal?

364
00:21:30.018 --> 00:21:33.601
I'm a con artist,
a schemer, not a criminal.


365
00:21:34.185 --> 00:21:35.018
You…

366
00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:39.601
You're just like the scammers
that extorted me, aren't you?


367
00:21:39.685 --> 00:21:40.976
No, I have ethics.

368
00:21:41.060 --> 00:21:42.685
My own ethics, but I do.

369
00:21:42.768 --> 00:21:45.685
I'd never steal a trailer
from an honest worker.


370
00:21:45.768 --> 00:21:48.518
Man, I want nothing to do with you.

371
00:21:49.143 --> 00:21:50.268
No way.

372
00:21:50.351 --> 00:21:52.810
As a matter of fact, #downwithclóvis.

373
00:21:52.893 --> 00:21:54.976
You shouldn't even have come.

374
00:21:55.060 --> 00:21:56.393
Good luck. Bye.

375
00:22:00.560 --> 00:22:02.268
Absolutely not.

376
00:22:02.893 --> 00:22:04.810
I won't ask a crook for help.

377
00:22:04.893 --> 00:22:08.310
I lost my trailer, but I won't do it.

378
00:22:08.393 --> 00:22:10.518
The world is already full of crooks.

379
00:22:10.601 --> 00:22:12.476
This country is full of crooks.

380
00:22:13.226 --> 00:22:14.435
You don't need me?

381
00:22:15.101 --> 00:22:16.435
I don't need you!

382
00:22:20.351 --> 00:22:21.685
Actually, I do.

383
00:22:23.018 --> 00:22:24.893
But God will help me.

384
00:22:28.685 --> 00:22:30.268
Just not yet.

385
00:22:31.893 --> 00:22:35.101
Eventually, He will.
I don't know when, but He will.


386
00:22:36.810 --> 00:22:38.060
I don't deserve this.

387
00:22:39.476 --> 00:22:40.893
I'm completely lost.

388
00:22:46.143 --> 00:22:47.476
That's Clóvis!

389
00:22:49.018 --> 00:22:52.726
-I don't have all day. Where are they?
-I'll find the documents.


390
00:22:53.268 --> 00:22:54.310
My gosh!

391
00:22:55.601 --> 00:22:56.768
What should I do?

392
00:22:58.560 --> 00:23:01.268
I can't find them.
They must be somewhere else.


393
00:23:01.351 --> 00:23:02.268
HIGHWAY PATROL

394
00:23:08.060 --> 00:23:11.185
Come back here, you bastard!

395
00:23:12.351 --> 00:23:15.810
I'm talking to you, scumbag! Asshole!

396
00:23:17.226 --> 00:23:18.310
Prick!

397
00:23:19.851 --> 00:23:20.893
Coward!

398
00:23:21.393 --> 00:23:24.018
You're a lying monster!

399
00:23:24.768 --> 00:23:27.018
You should've never been born!

400
00:23:27.601 --> 00:23:30.310
Sorry, I'll let you do your job
in a minute.


401
00:23:30.393 --> 00:23:32.143
Wait, who are you?

402
00:23:32.226 --> 00:23:33.101
Me?

403
00:23:33.810 --> 00:23:38.768
I'm the idiot who
fell for his sweet talk!

404
00:23:39.393 --> 00:23:41.560
You won't believe this.

405
00:23:43.018 --> 00:23:45.893
This man showed up at my dad's house

406
00:23:46.726 --> 00:23:48.310
and disgraced me!

407
00:23:51.643 --> 00:23:54.226
Okay, it was consensual,

408
00:23:55.268 --> 00:23:57.685
but he used me and ran away.

409
00:23:57.768 --> 00:23:58.893
It's not right!

410
00:23:58.976 --> 00:24:01.226
-Calm down, ma'am.
-Don't call me that!


411
00:24:01.310 --> 00:24:05.726
It reminds me of a book
I was forced to read when I was a kid.


412
00:24:06.310 --> 00:24:07.226
But I didn’t.

413
00:24:07.935 --> 00:24:09.018
I flunked out.

414
00:24:09.601 --> 00:24:11.976
-No, don't do that!
-She's hitting me.


415
00:24:12.060 --> 00:24:13.935
Do you feel sorry for him?

416
00:24:14.018 --> 00:24:17.851
You know what? Arrest me.
Take me away from society.


417
00:24:17.935 --> 00:24:20.435
Just don't make me
live with this crazy woman.


418
00:24:20.518 --> 00:24:23.101
She's crazy. You can all see that!

419
00:24:23.185 --> 00:24:25.351
He wants to be taken away

420
00:24:25.435 --> 00:24:29.393
because he doesn't want
to take responsibility as a father.


421
00:24:29.976 --> 00:24:33.060
-He doesn't want to raise his own child!
-What child?


422
00:24:33.143 --> 00:24:36.185
This one! Inside my belly.

423
00:24:36.268 --> 00:24:39.643
Since when is that a child?
That's a tapeworm!


424
00:24:39.726 --> 00:24:41.810
Do you want me to raise a tapeworm?

425
00:24:41.893 --> 00:24:44.393
Do you want me to christen a tapeworm?

426
00:24:44.476 --> 00:24:46.143
-It's a joke!
-My baby!


427
00:24:46.726 --> 00:24:50.601
Your dad is calling you names
before you're even born!


428
00:24:50.685 --> 00:24:54.726
Do you want the officer here
to force me to pay child support?


429
00:24:54.810 --> 00:24:57.185
-I do! Of course!
-Your mother is crazy!


430
00:24:57.268 --> 00:24:58.768
She is, trust your dad!

431
00:24:58.851 --> 00:24:59.976
You are crazy!

432
00:25:00.060 --> 00:25:03.393
You don't even know
if the baby is really yours!


433
00:25:03.476 --> 00:25:06.560
You are both insane!
Go fight somewhere else!


434
00:25:06.643 --> 00:25:09.976
No! Now I want to work this out.

435
00:25:10.060 --> 00:25:14.518
-No, sir! We are not doing anything here.
-We're going to work this out!


436
00:25:14.601 --> 00:25:17.643
I want to work
this out, brother. Got it?

437
00:25:17.726 --> 00:25:20.560
-I want to work this out!
-Enough!


438
00:25:20.643 --> 00:25:21.893
Enough!

439
00:25:21.976 --> 00:25:23.560
Move along, please,

440
00:25:23.643 --> 00:25:26.393
before I change my mind and arrest you.

441
00:25:26.476 --> 00:25:28.476
-Got it?
-Yes, you're right.


442
00:25:28.560 --> 00:25:29.518
Please.

443
00:25:29.601 --> 00:25:31.935
-Before my water breaks.
-Chill out.


444
00:25:32.018 --> 00:25:33.851
-It's all right, relax.
-Move.


445
00:25:33.935 --> 00:25:35.060
Everything is fine.

446
00:25:35.976 --> 00:25:37.768
I gotta hit the waves today.

447
00:25:47.726 --> 00:25:49.768
The tapeworm was a genius move.

448
00:25:49.851 --> 00:25:52.226
You couldn't believe it when I said that.

449
00:25:52.310 --> 00:25:55.018
I can't believe how you, Clóvis,

450
00:25:55.101 --> 00:25:57.643
such a quiet and shy boy,

451
00:25:57.726 --> 00:25:59.518
turned into a gangster.

452
00:26:00.268 --> 00:26:01.935
I was bullied, honey.

453
00:26:02.018 --> 00:26:04.351
Bullied! I was bullied.

454
00:26:04.435 --> 00:26:06.518
Lady Gaga was bullied, Madonna was.

455
00:26:06.601 --> 00:26:08.726
I heard Tom Cruise was bullied, too.

456
00:26:08.810 --> 00:26:10.518
All amazing people, like me.

457
00:26:10.601 --> 00:26:12.435
Thanks, bullying!

458
00:26:13.060 --> 00:26:14.976
When I was good, 
I got screwed.

459
00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:17.560
Now I'm bad, and things work out.
Isn't it better?


460
00:26:18.226 --> 00:26:19.060
Maybe.

461
00:26:19.893 --> 00:26:22.310
Look at you. You just fooled the police.

462
00:26:22.393 --> 00:26:23.851
You'll get me a trailer.

463
00:26:23.935 --> 00:26:25.393
-What?
-You heard me.


464
00:26:25.476 --> 00:26:27.976
I saved you. Now
you'll get me a trailer.

465
00:26:28.060 --> 00:26:28.893
Blackmail?

466
00:26:28.976 --> 00:26:30.518
You're my brother, Clóvis.

467
00:26:31.101 --> 00:26:33.935
I have nothing left.
Could you help me out?


468
00:26:40.935 --> 00:26:41.935
Okay.

469
00:26:42.893 --> 00:26:44.726
I'll figure something out.

470
00:26:44.810 --> 00:26:47.226
But after that, we'll part ways.

471
00:26:48.643 --> 00:26:50.560
Get off me. No!

472
00:26:53.143 --> 00:26:54.935
<i>What are you doing?</i>

473
00:26:55.018 --> 00:26:56.226
Making a reservation.

474
00:26:57.893 --> 00:26:59.643
Without any money in it?

475
00:27:00.518 --> 00:27:02.560
Let me explain one thing to you.

476
00:27:02.643 --> 00:27:04.101
I need my trailer,

477
00:27:04.185 --> 00:27:06.935
but I assumed you would get one honestly.

478
00:27:07.018 --> 00:27:09.226
You really did?

479
00:27:09.310 --> 00:27:10.310
How nice.

480
00:27:10.393 --> 00:27:12.393
Relax, it's just a magic trick.

481
00:27:12.476 --> 00:27:16.601
Instead of pulling a rabbit out of my hat,
I'll pull it out of someone else's hat.


482
00:27:26.310 --> 00:27:29.143
I won't stay here. Forget it.

483
00:27:29.226 --> 00:27:30.685
I have dignity.

484
00:27:31.351 --> 00:27:32.976
Great, because I'll stay.

485
00:27:38.226 --> 00:27:39.060
What's up?

486
00:27:39.143 --> 00:27:40.851
-Good morning.
-Good morning.


487
00:27:40.935 --> 00:27:42.976
-Do you have a reservation?
-I do.


488
00:27:43.060 --> 00:27:44.643
-How are you doing?
-Great.


489
00:27:44.726 --> 00:27:46.851
It's under the name Máximo Marques.

490
00:27:46.935 --> 00:27:48.976
I made a deposit earlier.

491
00:27:49.060 --> 00:27:53.685
I had a problem with my online account,
and I made the deposit at the bank.


492
00:27:53.768 --> 00:27:54.726
So annoying.

493
00:27:55.560 --> 00:27:58.810
