612
00:33:52.518 --> 00:33:54.476
Okay, hold it. God, help me.

613
00:33:56.393 --> 00:34:01.435
There's also Forte Beach,
which is our most famous beach.


614
00:34:01.518 --> 00:34:03.851
And our special trips, like Peró Beach.

615
00:34:03.935 --> 00:34:06.435
We have a 16-foot speedboat

616
00:34:06.518 --> 00:34:09.101
and a schooner that will be leaving soon,

617
00:34:09.185 --> 00:34:11.685
but we still have tickets for this trip.

618
00:34:12.685 --> 00:34:14.976
-Hi.
-Hi. I'm checking this mask out.


619
00:34:15.060 --> 00:34:18.976
If I wear this mask,
I'll scare all the fishes.


620
00:34:19.060 --> 00:34:21.226
I'll clear out the ocean.

621
00:34:21.310 --> 00:34:22.935
Like an extinction.

622
00:34:23.685 --> 00:34:27.726
Let me ask you.
Do you only have rides with 500 people?


623
00:34:27.810 --> 00:34:28.893
-No, we--
-What?


624
00:34:30.310 --> 00:34:34.851
Sorry. That's the fun part,

625
00:34:34.935 --> 00:34:37.101
I like it better that way. 
I prefer that.

626
00:34:37.185 --> 00:34:40.351
Do you have something more exclusive?

627
00:34:40.435 --> 00:34:42.143
Like a boat or a yacht?

628
00:34:42.226 --> 00:34:45.393
You could buy all the tickets
of a medium ride


629
00:34:45.476 --> 00:34:46.685
and take your friends.

630
00:34:46.768 --> 00:34:48.476
Great. How much is that?

631
00:34:48.560 --> 00:34:50.393
-A thousand reais.
-A thousand reais?


632
00:34:50.476 --> 00:34:51.518
Yeah, a thousand.

633
00:34:51.601 --> 00:34:55.018
To be on a boat alone,
without a single guy to flirt with?


634
00:34:56.226 --> 00:34:59.226
Well, I saw a sailor over there
with huge feet.


635
00:34:59.310 --> 00:35:02.976
Imagine him pulling the anchor
with those strong arms.


636
00:35:03.643 --> 00:35:04.893
Smart girl!

637
00:35:05.643 --> 00:35:06.851
I like-
- Sorry.

638
00:35:06.935 --> 00:35:08.768
Sorry, this is a private deal.

639
00:35:08.851 --> 00:35:10.935
-Do you take credit cards?
-I'll take a selfie.


640
00:35:11.018 --> 00:35:13.268
-No, just cash or check.
-Okay.


641
00:35:14.101 --> 00:35:16.393
-Great lighting.
-It's a beautiful day.


642
00:35:16.476 --> 00:35:17.893
It's wonderful.

643
00:35:17.976 --> 00:35:19.768
Very good.

644
00:35:20.935 --> 00:35:23.893
This is a good angle. Sorry.

645
00:35:26.393 --> 00:35:28.935
Some people don't know when to stop.

646
00:35:30.101 --> 00:35:34.185
Are you talking to me? Look at me, then.
Why are you looking at her?


647
00:35:34.268 --> 00:35:36.518
Such a snob. What an awful establishment!

648
00:35:36.601 --> 00:35:39.101
A seedy place with a smelly dog.

649
00:35:39.185 --> 00:35:40.768
Your dog is filthy.

650
00:35:40.851 --> 00:35:43.935
My goodness, that smell!

651
00:35:44.018 --> 00:35:46.893
What an awful establishment! My goodness.

652
00:35:52.393 --> 00:35:55.726
-Hello! Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon, how are you?


653
00:35:55.810 --> 00:35:58.393
I hope you're doing fine, because I'm not.

654
00:35:58.893 --> 00:36:00.393
My boss is pissed.

655
00:36:00.476 --> 00:36:03.226
I didn't introduce myself. I'm Wendell.

656
00:36:03.310 --> 00:36:07.935
I'm Silvia's driver,
who has just rented a boat, actually.


657
00:36:08.018 --> 00:36:10.476
-That lady.
-Exactly. Is your boss nice?


658
00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:11.768
