679
00:37:04.143 --> 00:37:07.393
-Hi, how are you? Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.


680
00:37:07.476 --> 00:37:11.060
So, what does it say on there?
"Eleven thousand reais," right?


681
00:37:11.851 --> 00:37:13.185
So, that's what it is.

682
00:37:13.268 --> 00:37:15.726
And it's urgent. 
I need this money.

683
00:37:15.810 --> 00:37:18.518
But first I need to contact the issuer.

684
00:37:18.601 --> 00:37:21.643
It's someone who suffers from Parkinson's.
Have you heard of it?


685
00:37:22.643 --> 00:37:25.143
I really need the bank's confirmation.

686
00:37:25.226 --> 00:37:26.101
All right.

687
00:37:26.185 --> 00:37:28.810
Ladies and gentlemen,
your attention, please.


688
00:37:28.893 --> 00:37:32.268
Sorry to bother you,
but I need to say something.


689
00:37:32.351 --> 00:37:35.976
The bank takes our money
but never gets us off, you know?


690
00:37:36.810 --> 00:37:40.393
My Aunt Silvia, who raised me,
has Parkinson's.


691
00:37:41.268 --> 00:37:45.643
The poor thing insisted
on using her own frail hands


692
00:37:45.726 --> 00:37:47.393
to write the check.

693
00:37:47.476 --> 00:37:52.101
She felt alive, she felt useful,
she felt active, you know?


694
00:37:52.185 --> 00:37:55.851
Because the check is a donation
from her to a child in need.


695
00:37:55.935 --> 00:37:59.143
However, she says her handwriting is bad.

696
00:37:59.226 --> 00:38:01.310
Of course, she has Parkinson's!

697
00:38:01.393 --> 00:38:03.976
-The number is squeezed up.
-You're lying!


698
00:38:04.060 --> 00:38:06.810
-I didn't say anything!
-Really?


699
00:38:06.893 --> 00:38:10.851
Now she didn't say anything.
She prefers the silence of cowardice.


700
00:38:10.935 --> 00:38:14.643
That's not on her behalf.
She's acting on the bank's behalf.


701
00:38:14.726 --> 00:38:18.560
She's not sparing her money.
She's sparing the bank's money!


702
00:38:18.643 --> 00:38:20.351
Does the bank spare us?

703
00:38:20.435 --> 00:38:22.643
-No!
-No, it doesn't!


704
00:38:22.726 --> 00:38:24.518
I wanna be a
bank in my next life.

705
00:38:24.601 --> 00:38:27.976
They're always forgiven,
but they never forgive anybody.


706
00:38:28.060 --> 00:38:30.726
Look at the special treatment line.

707
00:38:30.810 --> 00:38:32.143
Especially slow!

708
00:38:32.226 --> 00:38:36.101
It is outrageous to make seniors wait.

709
00:38:36.185 --> 00:38:38.726
It's horrible. 
They are elderly!

710
00:38:38.810 --> 00:38:42.101
Have you ever heard of the fourth age?

711
00:38:42.185 --> 00:38:44.185
No? Why? Because it doesn't exist!

712
00:38:44.726 --> 00:38:46.601
The third age is the last one!

713
00:38:46.685 --> 00:38:50.643
Every minute of their lives
is precious, you see?


714
00:38:50.726 --> 00:38:54.226
One of them might pass away right here.

715
00:38:54.310 --> 00:38:57.226
Look at her, eating anxiously.

716
00:38:57.310 --> 00:39:00.685
She's all anxious,
eating cookies, nonstop chewing.


717
00:39:00.768 --> 00:39:02.685
Her anxiety is the bank's fault.

718
00:39:02.768 --> 00:39:04.643
She stands there for hours,

719
00:39:04.726 --> 00:39:06.435
so she eats to pass the time.

720
00:39:06.518 --> 00:39:10.268
She was thin when she came in here.
Look at her now.


721
00:39:10.351 --> 00:39:12.601
She might explode right here.

722
00:39:12.685 --> 00:39:16.768
How about the revolving doors?
They are hell on Earth!


723
00:39:16.851 --> 00:39:20.435
We even give up coming in
for fear of getting stuck.


724
00:39:20.518 --> 00:39:22.226
