735
00:39:49.685 --> 00:39:51.143
Cash it!

736
00:39:51.226 --> 00:39:53.393
Cash his check!

737
00:39:54.060 --> 00:39:57.851
Listen to the voice of experience.
He is very experienced.


738
00:39:57.935 --> 00:39:59.601
Cash his check already!

739
00:39:59.685 --> 00:40:02.726
Even our chubby friend agrees.
I can say that. I'm chubby too.


740
00:40:02.810 --> 00:40:04.976
Cash it already!

741
00:40:05.060 --> 00:40:08.893
-Cash his check!
-Cash it!


742
00:40:08.976 --> 00:40:11.435
The giant has awakened.

743
00:40:11.518 --> 00:40:15.851
<i>Giant by thine own nature</i>

744
00:40:15.935 --> 00:40:19.351
<i>Thou art beautiful, strong</i>
<i>A fearless colossus</i>


745
00:40:19.435 --> 00:40:22.768
<i>And thy future mirrors that greatness</i>

746
00:40:22.851 --> 00:40:24.476
<i>Adored land</i>

747
00:40:24.560 --> 00:40:28.268
<i>Amongst a thousand others</i>
<i>Art thou, Brazil, beloved homeland</i>


748
00:40:28.351 --> 00:40:31.185
<i>Of the sons of this ground</i>
<i>Thou art kind mother</i>


749
00:40:31.268 --> 00:40:33.351
<i>Beloved homeland, Brazil!</i>

750
00:40:35.851 --> 00:40:36.851
Yeah!

751
00:40:39.726 --> 00:40:44.268
-Cash it!
-Cash it!


752
00:40:44.851 --> 00:40:45.851
I've got goosebumps.

753
00:40:48.226 --> 00:40:50.226
Didn't I say I'd rob a bank?

754
00:40:50.310 --> 00:40:52.601
-You robbed Silvia!
-What?


755
00:40:52.685 --> 00:40:54.518
She is the victim of a scam.

756
00:40:54.601 --> 00:40:57.351
The bank's loss is our gain.

757
00:40:57.435 --> 00:41:01.060
Eleven thousand reais, man!

758
00:41:01.143 --> 00:41:03.560
I've never seen so
much money in my life!

759
00:41:04.060 --> 00:41:05.810
-What's my share?
-None.


760
00:41:06.435 --> 00:41:08.226
You're getting greedy.

761
00:41:08.310 --> 00:41:10.726
I'll buy your trailer tomorrow.

762
00:41:11.310 --> 00:41:12.226
And then what?

763
00:41:12.310 --> 00:41:14.685
Then we'll part ways, as we agreed.

764
00:41:14.768 --> 00:41:15.601
No.

765
00:41:16.101 --> 00:41:17.935
I won't accept that.

766
00:41:18.018 --> 00:41:20.893
Didn't you come after
me to get a trailer?

767
00:41:20.976 --> 00:41:25.435
So, let's go out, have some fun.
When was the last time we did that?


768
00:41:25.518 --> 00:41:27.351
There's a party near the hotel.

769
00:41:27.435 --> 00:41:30.101
No way, the entire city is after us.

770
00:41:31.476 --> 00:41:32.685
Where are you going?

771
00:41:33.185 --> 00:41:36.893
To the sauna, to
relax after a hard day.

772
00:41:36.976 --> 00:41:39.976
Sauna? Let's party, man!

773
00:41:40.060 --> 00:41:41.810
No party, Lohane.

774
00:41:41.893 --> 00:41:43.518
We're done for today.

775
00:41:43.601 --> 00:41:45.768
I'll go to the sauna,
and you'll go to bed.


776
00:41:45.851 --> 00:41:48.101
-You'll lie down and rest.
-I will not!


777
00:41:48.185 --> 00:41:51.185
Because a woman of your age,
in your situation,


778
00:41:51.268 --> 00:41:52.435
is all wrong.

779
00:41:52.518 --> 00:41:54.601
What about my age?

780
00:41:55.851 --> 00:41:56.935
Clóvis?

781
00:41:58.101 --> 00:42:00.018
Clóvis, open the door!

782
00:42:00.101 --> 00:42:01.393
Clóvis!

783
00:42:10.685 --> 00:42:11.851
Lohane?

784
00:42:12.476 --> 00:42:13.351
Lohane.

785
00:42:13.976 --> 00:42:15.310
We need to talk.

786
00:42:16.435 --> 00:42:17.935
Lohane, answer me.

787
00:42:18.643 --> 00:42:19.643
Lohane.

788
00:42:21.185 --> 00:42:23.810
No way! I can't believe it!

789
00:42:33.851 --> 00:42:34.935
Lohane?

790
00:42:35.018 --> 00:42:36.768
Are you hitting on my wife?

791
00:42:36.851 --> 00:42:37.810
Are you serious?

792
00:42:37.893 --> 00:42:40.601
I won't even answer that. Look at me!

793
00:42:40.685 --> 00:42:42.101
I don't know your wife!

794
00:42:42.185 --> 00:42:45.393
Do you know why? She is a woman!
I'm not interested.


795
00:42:45.476 --> 00:42:46.560
Please.

796
00:42:47.893 --> 00:42:49.143
Where's that weirdo?

797
00:42:50.643 --> 00:42:53.851
-There she is. I found you!
-Ouch! Stop it!


798
00:42:53.935 --> 00:42:56.351
-Fugitive!
-I thought you were robbing me.


799
00:42:56.435 --> 00:42:57.893
Where are you going?

800
00:42:57.976 --> 00:43:00.226
I'm trying to get us in the party.

801
00:43:00.310 --> 00:43:03.351
-This lame party?
-Wait a minute, Clóvis!


802
00:43:03.435 --> 00:43:06.310
-Back to the hotel now!
-You're hurting me!


803
00:43:06.393 --> 00:43:09.310
-But I wanna go to the party!
-Stop it, girl.


804
00:43:09.393 --> 00:43:11.435
-Just a little bit, Clóvis!
-No way!


805
00:43:11.518 --> 00:43:14.143
-Please, just 30 minutes.
-Let go of my arm.


806
00:43:14.226 --> 00:43:15.976
-Let's have some fun!
-Get off me!


807
00:43:16.060 --> 00:43:17.851
-Come with me!
-Let me go now!


808
00:43:21.893 --> 00:43:23.060
Sorry.

809
00:43:24.351 --> 00:43:26.518
Look what you did, girl.

810
00:43:26.601 --> 00:43:29.476
You told me to let
you go, so I did.

811
00:43:29.560 --> 00:43:32.310
I just took a
shower, now I'm a mess.

812
00:43:32.393 --> 00:43:34.601
Look. I can't believe it, Lohane.

813
00:43:35.143 --> 00:43:36.101
Just look at it.

814
00:43:42.060 --> 00:43:43.393
It was not my fault.

815
00:43:44.351 --> 00:43:45.310
I want a hug.

816
00:43:45.393 --> 00:43:48.351
-No, Clóvis! Don't be resentful, wait!
-Hug me.


817
00:43:48.435 --> 00:43:51.560
You! You're the man who scammed me!

818
00:43:51.643 --> 00:43:52.476
Run!

819
00:43:52.560 --> 00:43:55.185
-She's crazy! Where's my check?
-Come back!


820
00:43:55.268 --> 00:43:57.060
-Where's my check?
-Get them!


821
00:43:57.143 --> 00:43:59.351
Stop those thieves!

822
00:44:00.726 --> 00:44:01.601
Run!

823
00:44:05.435 --> 00:44:09.310
See what you did, you idiot?
You should've listened to me.


824
00:44:09.393 --> 00:44:12.060
Now I won't even be able
to rest in this hotel.


825
00:44:12.143 --> 00:44:13.851
I'm so nervous!

826
00:44:13.935 --> 00:44:16.268
I can't go to jail, Clóvis!

827
00:44:16.351 --> 00:44:20.310
Listen, get our stuff from the room
and meet me at the car.


828
00:44:30.685 --> 00:44:32.185
May I help you?

829
00:44:32.268 --> 00:44:34.268
Hello, good evening. How are you?

830
00:44:34.351 --> 00:44:37.310
I would like to check out.

831
00:44:38.185 --> 00:44:39.935
Is there a problem?

832
00:44:40.018 --> 00:44:41.726
The hotel is a shithole.

833
00:44:41.810 --> 00:44:43.893
Actually, this city is a shithole.

834
00:44:43.976 --> 00:44:44.893
The state.

835
00:44:44.976 --> 00:44:46.310
The country.

836
00:44:46.393 --> 00:44:48.476
The planet is a shithole.

837
00:44:48.560 --> 00:44:51.268
If I could,
I'd check out of the Milky Way.


838
00:44:51.935 --> 00:44:54.435
But I can't even die. 
Where would I go?

839
00:44:54.518 --> 00:44:55.893
What if it's worse?

840
00:44:55.976 --> 00:44:57.810
Hurry up, kid. I have to go.

841
00:44:57.893 --> 00:45:00.060
So, will you cancel the deposit?

842
00:45:00.143 --> 00:45:02.435
Of course not. 
It's already been done.

843
00:45:02.518 --> 00:45:05.518
You'll get it on Monday.
Just refund the difference.


844
00:45:05.601 --> 00:45:07.643
I can't refund what we don't have.

845
00:45:07.726 --> 00:45:09.435
Listen up, kid.

846
00:45:09.935 --> 00:45:11.601
I'm already all dirty.

847
00:45:11.685 --> 00:45:14.643
Do you want to make it even worse?

848
00:45:14.726 --> 00:45:16.476
-Give my money back.
-No.


849
00:45:16.560 --> 00:45:17.935
Are you trying to scam me?

850
00:45:18.018 --> 00:45:20.476
I'll refund your money on Monday.

851
00:45:20.560 --> 00:45:23.976
I'll be far away from here on Monday,
so help me God.


852
00:45:24.060 --> 00:45:26.268
Not even all the sea here

853
00:45:26.351 --> 00:45:29.060
can wash away all the shit
that was done to me.


854
00:45:29.143 --> 00:45:30.768
Unfortunately, you must wait.

855
00:45:30.851 --> 00:45:32.810
Okay, I'll wait.

856
00:45:33.476 --> 00:45:35.935
But I'll sit so I won't get tired.

857
00:45:36.018 --> 00:45:38.060
No, sir, please.

858
00:45:38.143 --> 00:45:39.143
So nice.

859
00:45:39.226 --> 00:45:42.018
Don't do that, please.
For the love of God!


860
00:45:42.101 --> 00:45:45.351
-No, please.
-I am tired! I'm gonna lie down.


861
00:45:45.435 --> 00:45:48.601
-It's so comfortable. I'm sleepy.
-No, sir.


862
00:45:48.685 --> 00:45:51.226
-So good.
-For God's sake, don't do that!


863
00:45:51.310 --> 00:45:53.643
-Stand up, please!
-Okay.


864
00:45:53.726 --> 00:45:55.393
No problem, I'm sorry.

865
00:45:55.476 --> 00:45:56.560
I just ran into this.

866
00:45:56.643 --> 00:45:57.851
You'll pay for it!

867
00:46:00.435 --> 00:46:03.560
So, give me my money back!

868
00:46:06.226 --> 00:46:07.268
Wow, dude.

869
00:46:07.351 --> 00:46:09.685
We came out on top, Clóvis!

870
00:46:10.226 --> 00:46:13.268
Yesterday I was down, but today I'm rich!

871
00:46:13.351 --> 00:46:14.976
We came out on top?

872
00:46:15.601 --> 00:46:17.976
There's no "we." Who's "we"?

873
00:46:18.060 --> 00:46:20.893
We are different. 
You want other things.

874
00:46:20.976 --> 00:46:22.601
You just want to have fun,

875
00:46:22.685 --> 00:46:24.893
to party, you know?

876
00:46:24.976 --> 00:46:28.643
Not me. I'm all dirty.
I couldn't even take a shower.


877
00:46:29.476 --> 00:46:30.893
We're different, Lohane.

878
00:46:31.393 --> 00:46:33.768
I wanna be alone. 
I like it that way.

879
00:46:36.060 --> 00:46:37.060
Like Greta Garbo.

880
00:46:38.310 --> 00:46:41.935
I'll buy your trailer in the morning,
and then we're done.


881
00:46:44.060 --> 00:46:45.935
Why are you being so rude?

882
00:46:46.768 --> 00:46:47.893
Let's try to sleep.

883
00:47:08.810 --> 00:47:09.685
Nasty.

884
00:47:15.393 --> 00:47:16.768
This is your trailer.

885
00:47:19.310 --> 00:47:22.685
No, this is not a trailer.
I wanted a trailer.


886
00:47:22.768 --> 00:47:24.393
You wanted one, past tense.

887
00:47:24.476 --> 00:47:26.685
It's all we have. 
Don't you like it?

888
00:47:27.893 --> 00:47:30.976
Look, a trailer is ideal
for making burgers.


889
00:47:31.893 --> 00:47:34.101
Where is your Brazilian creativity?

890
00:47:34.185 --> 00:47:36.018
Where are your survival skills?

891
00:47:36.101 --> 00:47:38.393
We know how to reinvent ourselves!

892
00:47:38.476 --> 00:47:41.268
You can use this van
to come up with a deal.


893
00:47:41.351 --> 00:47:42.560
The Van Combo!

894
00:47:42.643 --> 00:47:44.935
I am tired of being Brazilian, then!

895
00:47:45.018 --> 00:47:46.435
That's your loss,

896
00:47:46.518 --> 00:47:49.185
because we've made
invaluable contributions.


897
00:47:49.268 --> 00:47:53.185
The airplane, wristwatches,
electronic voting, hair straightening


898
00:47:53.268 --> 00:47:56.768
and the most famous one,
the Brazilian wax.


899
00:47:56.851 --> 00:47:59.185
-The full bikini wax.
-No.


900
00:47:59.268 --> 00:48:04.226
A full bikini wax is awful for peeing
because the pee goes everywhere.


901
00:48:04.310 --> 00:48:06.851
-I don't need all this information.
-You do!


902
00:48:06.935 --> 00:48:10.185
Women suffer in these horrible bathrooms!

903
00:48:10.268 --> 00:48:13.060
We need to work our quadriceps to pee,

904
00:48:13.143 --> 00:48:15.643
and the stream
must be steady and straight.


905
00:48:15.726 --> 00:48:17.643
Okay, I don't wanna know that.

906
00:48:17.726 --> 00:48:18.935
Do we agree on the van?

907
00:48:21.226 --> 00:48:22.976
-Do I have a choice?
-No.


908
00:48:31.893 --> 00:48:33.435
So, this is it. Thank you.

909
00:48:35.101 --> 00:48:36.060
You're welcome.

910
00:48:36.560 --> 00:48:37.726
It was my pleasure.

911
00:48:39.351 --> 00:48:40.476
See you around?

912
00:48:40.560 --> 00:48:42.935
Maybe. Life is unpredictable.

913
00:48:43.560 --> 00:48:44.518
Okay, then.

914
00:48:44.601 --> 00:48:45.810
All right, then.

915
00:48:46.393 --> 00:48:47.310
Great.

916
00:48:47.393 --> 00:48:48.310
Great, then.

917
00:48:48.810 --> 00:48:50.560
Goodbye.

918
00:48:51.476 --> 00:48:53.226
Now is goodbye for real.

919
00:48:53.810 --> 00:48:56.768
Good luck, Clóvis. Take care.

920
00:48:56.851 --> 00:48:57.851
You too.

921
00:49:12.476 --> 00:49:15.268
<i>I didn't learn to say goodbye</i>

922
00:49:16.726 --> 00:49:20.851
<i>I don't know if I
will ever get used to it</i>

923
00:49:21.351 --> 00:49:24.060
<i>Looking right into your eyes</i>

924
00:49:24.143 --> 00:49:26.185
<i>I know it will be engraved in mine</i>

925
00:49:26.268 --> 00:49:29.393
<i>The stare in your eyes</i>

926
00:49:30.268 --> 00:49:33.435
<i>I have nothing to say</i>

927
00:49:35.393 --> 00:49:36.643
What the fuck?

928
00:49:39.518 --> 00:49:41.893
Are you insane? 
What are you doing?

929
00:49:41.976 --> 00:49:43.310
You gave me a van.

930
00:49:43.393 --> 00:49:46.351
You promised me a trailer.
I want a trailer!


931
00:49:46.435 --> 00:49:47.976
Stop complaining!

932
00:49:48.060 --> 00:49:49.518
This is a piece of shit!

933
00:49:49.601 --> 00:49:52.393
I gave you what
I could. Just take it!

934
00:49:52.476 --> 00:49:56.143
You said you'd give me a trailer.
I want my trailer!


935
00:49:56.226 --> 00:49:58.226
-I won't!
-Yes, you will!


936
00:49:58.310 --> 00:50:00.226
-You're stupid!
-No, you are!


937
00:50:16.268 --> 00:50:18.893
Damn it!

938
00:50:19.393 --> 00:50:20.351
What the fuck?

939
00:50:22.351 --> 00:50:24.060
I can't believe it.

940
00:50:25.601 --> 00:50:26.476
Fuck!

941
00:50:43.101 --> 00:50:45.226
Change the station. 
This song sucks.

942
00:50:45.810 --> 00:50:46.976
I like it.

943
00:50:47.060 --> 00:50:48.768
I also liked my car.

944
00:50:48.851 --> 00:50:52.101
But I had to leave it behind
with a blown engine.


945
00:50:52.185 --> 00:50:53.685
You are so grumpy.

946
00:50:54.226 --> 00:50:55.143
My God, Clóvis.

947
00:50:55.226 --> 00:50:58.060
Let's celebrate
that our family is together again!


948
00:50:58.143 --> 00:51:00.726
What? I'm only here
because I need to be.

949
00:51:01.226 --> 00:51:05.935
You hung on to me like a disease,
a virus. I'll get rid of you soon.


950
00:51:06.018 --> 00:51:10.226
I'm having some technical difficulties.
Can someone hear me?


951
00:51:13.435 --> 00:51:14.393
I love this one!

952
00:51:15.393 --> 00:51:17.976
Man, this song is awesome.

953
00:51:18.060 --> 00:51:19.101
So good.

954
00:51:19.185 --> 00:51:21.601
This is a song for driving, for freedom.

955
00:51:21.685 --> 00:51:23.393
Feel the freedom.

956
00:51:23.476 --> 00:51:26.018
The cops are after me, remember?

957
00:51:26.893 --> 00:51:28.310
You're so pessimistic.

958
00:51:28.393 --> 00:51:29.851
It attracts negativity.

959
00:51:29.935 --> 00:51:32.560
You're too serious, too grumpy.

960
00:51:32.643 --> 00:51:34.518
You need to enjoy life.

961
00:51:35.185 --> 00:51:36.476
You want me to enjoy?

962
00:51:36.976 --> 00:51:38.310
Want me to live?

963
00:51:38.393 --> 00:51:40.018
-That's what you want?
-Yes.


964
00:51:40.101 --> 00:51:42.768
-Do you want freedom? Okay.
-Freedom.


965
00:51:46.310 --> 00:51:47.518
Freedom!

966
00:51:48.101 --> 00:51:49.935
Excitement!

967
00:51:51.976 --> 00:51:52.810
There you go.

968
00:51:53.393 --> 00:51:56.518
I felt nothing.
My life didn't change one bit.


969
00:51:56.601 --> 00:51:59.018
You didn't really mean it.

970
00:51:59.101 --> 00:52:01.768
You didn't let yourself
be completely free.


971
00:52:02.518 --> 00:52:03.685
Look at me.

972
00:52:03.768 --> 00:52:06.935
I'm totally lost,
sitting next to a criminal,


973
00:52:07.476 --> 00:52:10.601
but I'm here physically and spiritually.

974
00:52:11.851 --> 00:52:13.518
-You want me to let go?
-Yes.


975
00:52:13.601 --> 00:52:14.851
And live?

976
00:52:14.935 --> 00:52:16.935
All you do is criticize.

977
00:52:17.018 --> 00:52:20.185
It was just some advice.
You don't have to do it.


978
00:52:20.268 --> 00:52:23.851
If freedom is what you want,
freedom is what you'll get.


979
00:52:27.351 --> 00:52:30.268
<i>Tell people I'm here…</i>

980
00:52:30.351 --> 00:52:32.060
Set me free, DJ!

981
00:52:32.143 --> 00:52:35.351
<i>So take risks, kiss, make mistakes</i>

982
00:52:35.435 --> 00:52:37.810
<i>Love doesn't come with a warning sign</i>

983
00:52:37.893 --> 00:52:42.268
<i>Tell people I'm here</i>
<i>We only live once</i>


984
00:52:42.351 --> 00:52:44.726
Lohane!

985
00:52:45.518 --> 00:52:47.685
Lohane! Pay attention!

986
00:53:58.476 --> 00:53:59.435
I'm done!

987
00:53:59.518 --> 00:54:01.768
It's been hard to live like this!

988
00:54:01.851 --> 00:54:02.726
Very hard!

989
00:54:02.810 --> 00:54:05.726
After this incarnation,
spare me from coming back.


990
00:54:05.810 --> 00:54:08.393
There's nothing left for me to endure!

991
00:54:09.060 --> 00:54:09.893
Come on.

992
00:54:12.726 --> 00:54:14.268
I'm sorry, Clóvis.

993
00:54:15.726 --> 00:54:16.560
Fuck!

994
00:54:31.393 --> 00:54:33.226
Clóvis, I'm hungry.

995
00:54:33.768 --> 00:54:35.018
Aren't you?

996
00:54:37.018 --> 00:54:38.268
I'm talking to you.

997
00:54:38.976 --> 00:54:41.685
-Talk to my foot!
-Your foot reeks!


998
00:54:41.768 --> 00:54:42.935
Your past reeks.

999
00:54:43.643 --> 00:54:46.018
-It's the same as yours.
-Absolutely not.


1000
00:54:46.101 --> 00:54:48.435
I grew up, I evolved, I moved on.

1001
00:54:48.518 --> 00:54:51.226
My life went downhill because of you.

1002
00:54:51.310 --> 00:54:53.310
Clóvis, don't lie.

1003
00:54:53.393 --> 00:54:56.310
The cops were after you,
and I saved you, darling.


1004
00:54:56.393 --> 00:54:58.101
I brought joy to your life.

1005
00:54:58.185 --> 00:55:00.893
Turn that off.
I don't want to talk to you.


1006
00:55:00.976 --> 00:55:02.226
Talk to my foot.

1007
00:55:17.351 --> 00:55:19.810
Lohane.

1008
00:55:20.351 --> 00:55:22.351
-What is it?
-A mosquito.


1009
00:55:22.435 --> 00:55:25.268
-Leave it, man.
-I'm serious. I need it.


1010
00:55:25.351 --> 00:55:26.560
-For what?
-Eating.


1011
00:55:26.643 --> 00:55:28.018
-A mosquito?
-Stop!


1012
00:55:28.101 --> 00:55:29.018
Don't move.

1013
00:55:29.101 --> 00:55:30.643
I'm not moving, Clóvis.

1014
00:55:31.268 --> 00:55:34.018
I'm actually numb from starvation.

1015
00:55:34.101 --> 00:55:36.768
My stomach is eating itself.

1016
00:55:36.851 --> 00:55:40.893
If I put any food in my mouth,
it will disintegrate.


1017
00:55:41.518 --> 00:55:42.351
It landed.

1018
00:55:44.685 --> 00:55:46.435
What was that, Clóvis?

1019
00:55:47.143 --> 00:55:48.643
That's a crime.

1020
00:55:49.226 --> 00:55:51.851
That's domestic battery.

1021
00:55:51.935 --> 00:55:57.893
People do say assaults happen
in the family, at home!


1022
00:55:57.976 --> 00:55:59.226
What home, girl?

1023
00:55:59.310 --> 00:56:00.935
Is this a home? Since when?

1024
00:56:01.560 --> 00:56:03.101
We've hit rock bottom.

1025
00:56:03.185 --> 00:56:05.143
It's not about the trailer

1026
00:56:05.226 --> 00:56:07.101
or getting rich.

1027
00:56:07.185 --> 00:56:10.101
-No?
-No, it's the law of the jungle.


1028
00:56:10.185 --> 00:56:11.810
It's about survival.

1029
00:56:11.893 --> 00:56:13.560
It's about not starving.

1030
00:56:16.810 --> 00:56:18.143
Where are you going?

1031
00:56:18.226 --> 00:56:19.310
To look for food.

1032
00:56:19.393 --> 00:56:21.935
-And I'll be here, starving?
-I don't know!


1033
00:56:22.018 --> 00:56:25.351
I'm not your guardian.
I won't feed a couch potato.


1034
00:56:25.435 --> 00:56:27.018
I'm no such thing!

1035
00:56:27.101 --> 00:56:30.935
I have a business, Clóvis.
I'm a small business owner.


1036
00:56:31.018 --> 00:56:34.226
Small indeed, microscopic.
No one even knows it exists.


1037
00:56:34.310 --> 00:56:37.560
I don't wanna listen to you.
I don't care about you!


1038
00:56:37.643 --> 00:56:40.518
DJ, turn on the music! Hit it!

1039
00:56:45.060 --> 00:56:47.226
<i>People are scared</i>

1040
00:56:47.310 --> 00:56:50.351
<i>after two scammers arrived</i>
<i>in the Lakes Region</i>


1041
00:56:50.435 --> 00:56:52.310
<i>and started committing crimes.</i>

1042
00:56:52.393 --> 00:56:54.976
Clóvis! Come back here, hurry!

1043
00:56:55.060 --> 00:56:57.560
<i>They've already scammed a travel agency,</i>

1044
00:56:57.643 --> 00:57:00.935
<i>a bank and a luxury hotel</i>
<i>in Arraial do Cabo.</i>


1045
00:57:01.018 --> 00:57:02.310
-What is it?
-Listen.


1046
00:57:02.393 --> 00:57:05.851
<i>The city security cameras</i>
<i>caught them in action.</i>


1047
00:57:05.935 --> 00:57:07.643
<i>The police have been informed</i>

1048
00:57:07.726 --> 00:57:10.310
<i>and the footage will help</i>
<i>the investigation.</i>


1049
00:57:12.935 --> 00:57:13.851
Clóvis!

1050
00:57:15.351 --> 00:57:17.310
We went too far.

1051
00:57:17.393 --> 00:57:19.643
We lost control, Clóvis!

1052
00:57:20.351 --> 00:57:22.185
Why didn't we study more?

1053
00:57:22.268 --> 00:57:24.351
I could've been a doctor, a lawyer.

1054
00:57:24.435 --> 00:57:27.726
I could be in a courthouse,
but look at me!


1055
00:57:31.185 --> 00:57:32.518
What did you say?

1056
00:57:37.435 --> 00:57:38.851
I wanted to be a doctor.

1057
00:57:42.060 --> 00:57:43.143
The problem is

1058
00:57:43.726 --> 00:57:46.601
between my current self
and my doctor self,


1059
00:57:46.685 --> 00:57:50.268
there's a medical school
that takes eight years.


1060
00:57:50.351 --> 00:57:53.226
What should help me get closer
to practicing medicine


1061
00:57:53.310 --> 00:57:54.893
is what keeps me away.

1062
00:57:54.976 --> 00:57:57.226
Life is so crazy.

1063
00:57:58.768 --> 00:57:59.768
So crazy.

1064
00:58:04.060 --> 00:58:05.976
I know how we'll get out of here.

1065
00:58:07.601 --> 00:58:09.935
UMBERTO MODIANO AIRPORT

1066
00:58:11.685 --> 00:58:12.935
DEPARTURES

1067
00:58:13.810 --> 00:58:17.601
-Emergency!
-It's a transplant, excuse us.


1068
00:58:17.685 --> 00:58:20.185
-It's an emergency.
-We have to board now.


1069
00:58:20.268 --> 00:58:22.976
-I wasn't informed.
-I'm informing you now.


1070
00:58:23.060 --> 00:58:26.476
There are specific logistics
for this procedure.


1071
00:58:29.018 --> 00:58:30.893
Do you know what the world needs?

1072
00:58:30.976 --> 00:58:33.143
A heart! What is in here? A heart!

1073
00:58:33.226 --> 00:58:36.560
A person is dying,
and you're wasting our time!


1074
00:58:36.643 --> 00:58:38.851
The Air Force does that, ma'am.

1075
00:58:38.935 --> 00:58:42.601
It transports politicians.
They don't even have a heart!


1076
00:58:42.685 --> 00:58:46.226
The Air Force sent us,
and you send us back to the Air Force?


1077
00:58:46.310 --> 00:58:47.351
What should I do?

1078
00:58:47.435 --> 00:58:49.476
Ask Santa Claus for a sleigh?

1079
00:58:49.560 --> 00:58:50.393
Is that so?

1080
00:58:50.476 --> 00:58:53.018
This is an outrage!
I can't board the plane!


1081
00:58:53.101 --> 00:58:55.726
-An outrage!
-An outrage!


1082
00:58:55.810 --> 00:58:58.810
Fine, the flight isn't full.

1083
00:58:58.893 --> 00:59:00.685
-Documents, please.
-Here.


1084
00:59:28.851 --> 00:59:31.018
I can't believe we did it!

1085
00:59:31.101 --> 00:59:35.018
Can you speak louder?
Do you want to get arrested now or later?


1086
00:59:35.101 --> 00:59:38.310
-What? I didn't do anything.
-Yes, now you're a saint.


1087
00:59:40.143 --> 00:59:42.060
-I'm going to the restroom.
-Go ahead.


1088
00:59:43.268 --> 00:59:46.768
-Stay here. I don't know this city.
-Fine.


1089
00:59:46.851 --> 00:59:50.643
If you leave me, they'll find me
in ten years with dreadlocks.


1090
00:59:50.726 --> 00:59:52.393
-A hobo.
-Hurry up, girl.


1091
00:59:54.393 --> 00:59:55.476
A vagrant!

1092
00:59:55.560 --> 00:59:56.643
Just go already!

1093
01:00:09.476 --> 01:00:10.310
Clóvis.

1094
01:00:11.601 --> 01:00:13.476
-You're under arrest.
-Shit.


1095
01:00:14.226 --> 01:00:15.060
Fuck.

1096
01:00:17.018 --> 01:00:20.393
Hurry up. What is taking so long?

1097
01:00:20.476 --> 01:00:24.060
They can't even arrest people efficiently
in this country.


1098
01:00:24.143 --> 01:00:25.393
Come on!

1099
01:00:31.726 --> 01:00:32.560
Clóvis?

1100
01:00:45.435 --> 01:00:48.101
CLÓVIS CARDOZO GOMES
ADMITTANCE: 04-14-2017


1101
01:00:51.101 --> 01:00:56.268
<i>In jail, with no money, without Lohane,</i>
<i>and with that crazy bearded guy beside me.</i>


1102
01:00:56.351 --> 01:00:58.268
<i>It would be the end for anyone,</i>

1103
01:00:58.351 --> 01:01:01.518
<i>but a real con artist never gives up.</i>

1104
01:01:01.601 --> 01:01:03.601
You know you're done, right?

1105
01:01:04.935 --> 01:01:07.351
Based on your criminal record,

1106
01:01:07.435 --> 01:01:11.101
you will spend, I don't know,
about 20 years in prison.


1107
01:01:11.185 --> 01:01:14.018
-Let's talk it over.
-I won't talk to you.


1108
01:01:14.101 --> 01:01:15.601
Nunes, just take him.

1109
01:01:15.685 --> 01:01:17.810
If I help you, will you help me?

1110
01:01:17.893 --> 01:01:19.810
Help me? You can't even help yourself.

1111
01:01:19.893 --> 01:01:23.685
Tell me. Do you think
this guy has something to offer me?


1112
01:01:23.768 --> 01:01:24.643
Scumbag.

1113
01:01:26.643 --> 01:01:28.476
<i>Two hundred years ago</i>,

1114
01:01:28.560 --> 01:01:32.143
<i>an ensign got outraged</i>
<i>by the injustices of the Portuguese Crown</i>


1115
01:01:32.226 --> 01:01:34.268
<i>and fought for our freedom.</i>

1116
01:01:34.351 --> 01:01:36.893
<i>But his own accomplices turned him in.</i>

1117
01:01:36.976 --> 01:01:41.185
<i>He was hanged, quartered,</i>
<i>and his remains were publicly displayed.</i>


1118
01:01:41.768 --> 01:01:44.768
<i>The traitors were acquitted by the queen.</i>

1119
01:01:44.851 --> 01:01:47.643
<i>The title has gained</i>
<i>several synonyms since:</i>


1120
01:01:47.726 --> 01:01:51.101
<i>snitch, tattletale, narc,</i>
<i>whistle-blower, rat.</i>


1121
01:01:51.185 --> 01:01:53.560
<i>Recently, it received a much cooler one:</i>

1122
01:01:53.643 --> 01:01:56.351
Plea bargaining.

1123
01:01:58.768 --> 01:02:00.143
Let me talk to him.

1124
01:02:01.643 --> 01:02:03.393
It's trending.

1125
01:02:03.476 --> 01:02:05.060
Everybody's doing it.

1126
01:02:05.601 --> 01:02:07.851
I can't miss out on this.

1127
01:02:07.935 --> 01:02:10.143
Neither can you, right?

1128
01:02:12.226 --> 01:02:13.060
Spit it out.

1129
01:02:13.143 --> 01:02:15.560
I'll do it only if
I can get a pardon.

1130
01:02:16.435 --> 01:02:18.393
What are you talking about?

1131
01:02:18.476 --> 01:02:20.018
A Federal Senator.

1132
01:02:21.643 --> 01:02:22.560
Go on.

1133
01:02:22.643 --> 01:02:26.185
There's a money-laundering scheme
involving fake works of art.


1134
01:02:26.268 --> 01:02:29.518
I know about it because I'm involved,
the counterfeiter.


1135
01:02:29.601 --> 01:02:32.560
Nice to meet you.
I'm the artist, actually.


1136
01:02:32.643 --> 01:02:36.435
Who is always undermined,
unappreciated, who's paid less…


1137
01:02:36.518 --> 01:02:38.310
But let's not talk about that.

1138
01:02:38.851 --> 01:02:40.893
I am willing to cooperate,

1139
01:02:41.685 --> 01:02:45.226
and you can catch
not only a small fish like myself,


1140
01:02:46.268 --> 01:02:47.643
but a shark.

1141
01:02:48.601 --> 01:02:51.060
A shark! That's right.

1142
01:02:53.810 --> 01:02:55.060
-Nunes!
-What?


1143
01:02:55.810 --> 01:02:57.476
Have you ever eaten a shark?

1144
01:03:01.893 --> 01:03:05.351
Listen, you deadbeat,
the feds have joined the case.


1145
01:03:06.226 --> 01:03:07.060
You see?

1146
01:03:07.143 --> 01:03:10.601
Do you think this ankle bracelet
is just an accessory?


1147
01:03:11.185 --> 01:03:13.435
You are being monitored 24/7.

1148
01:03:14.018 --> 01:03:17.060
I promised to deliver
the Senator's head on a platter,


1149
01:03:17.143 --> 01:03:19.685
so don't think about screwing me over.

1150
01:03:19.768 --> 01:03:22.851
Relax, I won't do anything
behind your back.


1151
01:03:24.310 --> 01:03:25.226
One more thing.

1152
01:03:26.935 --> 01:03:29.143
If something goes wrong, you're done.

1153
01:03:29.226 --> 01:03:31.601
And not for 20
years, you'll be a lifer.

1154
01:03:32.518 --> 01:03:35.560
Everything will work out
just fine, deputy.


1155
01:03:35.643 --> 01:03:37.976
Think about your promotion.

1156
01:03:38.060 --> 01:03:39.893
Hey, take this.

1157
01:03:41.185 --> 01:03:44.060
I have a copy. One week.

1158
01:03:44.143 --> 01:03:46.018
That's all you got. One week.

1159
01:03:50.226 --> 01:03:52.226
Lohane? Where are you?

1160
01:04:00.435 --> 01:04:03.226
The check scam
is working here in São Paulo.


1161
01:04:03.310 --> 01:04:05.851
-I almost fell for it.
-I created a monster.


1162
01:04:05.935 --> 01:04:08.143
No, you didn't create a monster,

1163
01:04:08.226 --> 01:04:12.018
you gave birth to a monster
and left it in the gutter.


1164
01:04:12.101 --> 01:04:14.268
I told you not to leave me.

1165
01:04:14.351 --> 01:04:17.226
Luckily, I'm very charming.

1166
01:04:17.310 --> 01:04:18.685
Hi there!

1167
01:04:18.768 --> 01:04:20.268
Will you let me talk?

1168
01:04:20.393 --> 01:04:22.560
Clóvis, I'm not gonna be mad at you

1169
01:04:22.643 --> 01:04:25.518
only because I left
with nothing but my clothes,


1170
01:04:25.601 --> 01:04:28.435
and now I'm here, looking stunning,

1171
01:04:28.518 --> 01:04:30.976
in one of the biggest cities, São Paulo,

1172
01:04:31.060 --> 01:04:34.643
and I'm on the lookout
for better opportunities…


1173
01:04:35.851 --> 01:04:37.435
if you know what I mean.

1174
01:04:37.518 --> 01:04:38.851
Lohane, where are you?

1175
01:04:38.935 --> 01:04:40.018
<i>Where am I?</i>

1176
01:04:40.101 --> 01:04:42.601
I'm on Oscar.

1177
01:04:43.185 --> 01:04:44.726
Oscar Freire.

1178
01:04:45.310 --> 01:04:48.560
You were not delusional,
you're right. We're siblings.


1179
01:04:48.643 --> 01:04:50.143
Siblings fight, you know?

1180
01:04:50.226 --> 01:04:55.018
They get angry, argue,
say they won't speak to each other again.


1181
01:04:55.101 --> 01:04:57.810
-Thirty minutes later, it's all fine.
-Thirty?


1182
01:04:58.476 --> 01:05:01.518
I spent a hell of a night alone
in São Paulo.


1183
01:05:02.143 --> 01:05:04.351
-I saw terrible things.
-Listen.


1184
01:05:04.435 --> 01:05:08.268
I had to sort some things out
and find a place for us to stay.


1185
01:05:08.351 --> 01:05:12.351
And now I'm here to take you
to this apartment I got.


1186
01:05:12.435 --> 01:05:15.268
-You already did that?
-I have connections.


1187
01:05:15.351 --> 01:05:18.226
Now let's go,
because we really are siblings.


1188
01:05:18.310 --> 01:05:21.310
We are family,
and I have a proposition for you.


1189
01:05:21.393 --> 01:05:23.101
Proposition?

1190
01:05:23.185 --> 01:05:25.268
Our last scam together.

1191
01:05:25.351 --> 01:05:26.185
A big one.

1192
01:05:27.393 --> 01:05:29.060
I knew it, Clóvis.

1193
01:05:29.143 --> 01:05:34.101
When you talked about siblings and family,
I knew you were up to something.


1194
01:05:34.685 --> 01:05:36.268
Unfortunately, I can't.

1195
01:05:36.351 --> 01:05:39.893
I have an event
that cannot be postponed, my life!


1196
01:05:39.976 --> 01:05:41.643
I can't miss it.

1197
01:05:41.726 --> 01:05:46.518
If I survived 24 hours here without you,
I can survive the entire month.


1198
01:05:46.601 --> 01:05:48.018
It's not about survival,

1199
01:05:48.101 --> 01:05:51.768
I'm talking about something big.
A lot of money.


1200
01:05:52.726 --> 01:05:54.643
Impossible. How much?

1201
01:05:55.643 --> 01:05:58.726
You know that I've always liked to draw.

1202
01:06:02.185 --> 01:06:04.935
<i>Eventually I became a really good painter.</i>

1203
01:06:05.851 --> 01:06:09.393
<i>So good that</i>
<i>I counterfeited famous paintings.</i>


1204
01:06:10.185 --> 01:06:14.060
<i>I got in touch with a Senator</i>
<i>who liked to buy these paintings.</i>


1205
01:06:14.643 --> 01:06:18.435
<i>Then I sold him a fake painting</i>
<i>for really good money.</i>


1206
01:06:18.518 --> 01:06:22.476
<i>But that man broke into my apartment,</i>
<i>got all his money back,</i>


1207
01:06:22.560 --> 01:06:25.476
<i>and stole the money I made</i>
<i>selling the Christ.</i>


1208
01:06:26.435 --> 01:06:30.810
<i>That's why I was running away</i>
<i>the day you showed up and I ran over you.</i>


1209
01:06:32.643 --> 01:06:35.935
An art counterfeiter?

1210
01:06:36.018 --> 01:06:36.935
Yeah.

1211
01:06:37.018 --> 01:06:37.851
My God.

1212
01:06:38.560 --> 01:06:41.351
You never cease to amaze me.

1213
01:06:41.435 --> 01:06:43.810
We just need to
sell him a new painting.

1214
01:06:43.893 --> 01:06:44.976
And he pays well.

1215
01:06:45.060 --> 01:06:48.518
I'll do everything perfectly,
as I always do.


1216
01:06:48.601 --> 01:06:50.893
But he knows me,
he already screwed me over,


1217
01:06:50.976 --> 01:06:52.935
so I need a new
guy to talk to him.

1218
01:06:53.018 --> 01:06:56.101
Or a new girl. You, dear.

1219
01:06:56.185 --> 01:06:58.268
No. No way.

1220
01:06:58.893 --> 01:07:03.851
Listen, you want to do business
with the big shot who screwed you over?


1221
01:07:04.435 --> 01:07:07.101
What do you want me to do,
jump off a bridge?


1222
01:07:07.185 --> 01:07:09.351
Gargle with the Tietê River's water?
No way!


1223
01:07:09.435 --> 01:07:12.018
-What else do you want?
-It'll work this time.


1224
01:07:12.101 --> 01:07:15.185
You just need to sell the painting
and get the money.


1225
01:07:15.685 --> 01:07:17.060
Trust me on this.

1226
01:07:18.310 --> 01:07:20.101
It's the last scam, I promise.

1227
01:07:20.185 --> 01:07:21.893
We'll have a better life.

1228
01:07:22.685 --> 01:07:23.518
Trust me.

1229
01:07:25.393 --> 01:07:26.976
Will I get half of the money?

1230
01:07:27.060 --> 01:07:28.226
Of course!

1231
