a brand-new trailer and much more.


1232
01:07:31.643 --> 01:07:36.226
No, you'll buy it with your share,
as promised.


1233
01:07:36.310 --> 01:07:40.393
You'll give me my share,
and then you'll buy a trailer with yours.


1234
01:07:41.185 --> 01:07:42.351
Such a smart-ass.

1235
01:07:42.435 --> 01:07:44.435
I had a good teacher.

1236
01:07:45.351 --> 01:07:46.351
Fine.

1237
01:07:48.768 --> 01:07:49.768
It's a deal.

1238
01:07:49.851 --> 01:07:50.976
<i>Abaporu.</i>

1239
01:07:51.060 --> 01:07:54.768
One of the most important paintings
in the history of art.


1240
01:07:54.851 --> 01:07:57.893
It was bought at an auction
for $2,5 million.


1241
01:07:57.976 --> 01:08:01.018
-More than six million reais.
-Too expensive.


1242
01:08:01.101 --> 01:08:03.851
-It's worth $30 million today.
-Damn! Thirty?


1243
01:08:03.935 --> 01:08:06.643
And my burgers are three bucks a pop.

1244
01:08:06.726 --> 01:08:08.893
It was painted by Tarsila do Amaral.

1245
01:08:08.976 --> 01:08:10.310
Tarsila? Who is she?

1246
01:08:10.393 --> 01:08:12.351
Tarsila was modern.

1247
01:08:12.435 --> 01:08:15.226
I think of myself as modern, too, Clóvis.

1248
01:08:15.310 --> 01:08:19.310
-She had a clean technique.
-I mastered that technique.


1249
01:08:19.393 --> 01:08:21.518
My bank account is all cleaned up.

1250
01:08:21.601 --> 01:08:24.601
Look, write down
she had a Brazilwood phase.


1251
01:08:24.685 --> 01:08:26.476
So lucky.

1252
01:08:26.560 --> 01:08:29.601
I've never gotten out of that phase.

1253
01:08:29.685 --> 01:08:34.226
I've been in that phase for ages,
I've never seen foreign wood.


1254
01:08:34.310 --> 01:08:35.476
Listen up.

1255
01:08:36.060 --> 01:08:37.601
You must be convincing.

1256
01:08:37.685 --> 01:08:38.643
-Okay.
-Okay?


1257
01:08:38.726 --> 01:08:40.768
I'll paint a Portinari now.

1258
01:08:42.310 --> 01:08:43.143
Who?

1259
01:08:44.018 --> 01:08:45.143
Girl…

1260
01:08:47.893 --> 01:08:51.351
Impressionism, expressionism,
cubism, and surrealism, go!


1261
01:08:51.435 --> 01:08:55.435
Impressionists paint
their impression of reality. It's boring.


1262
01:08:55.518 --> 01:08:58.851
Expressionists express
their suffering, their emotions.


1263
01:08:58.935 --> 01:09:02.476
They get drunk,
and their paintings are wonky. I like it.


1264
01:09:12.518 --> 01:09:14.268
