1458
01:20:44.060 --> 01:20:47.101
Which one? Mine or the Senator's?

1459
01:20:47.185 --> 01:20:48.768
Or both?

1460
01:20:48.851 --> 01:20:50.268
Which one is faker?

1461
01:20:51.226 --> 01:20:54.851
-Arrest him, deputy.
-He is insane! Security!


1462
01:20:54.935 --> 01:20:58.060
Attention, everyone. 
The auction is over!

1463
01:20:59.976 --> 01:21:01.018
What?

1464
01:21:01.101 --> 01:21:02.060
What's going on?

1465
01:21:02.143 --> 01:21:04.935
Please leave
in a calm and organized manner.


1466
01:21:05.018 --> 01:21:06.643
I'll get your statements.

1467
01:21:07.185 --> 01:21:09.393
Not you, Senator. 
Wait a minute.

1468
01:21:09.476 --> 01:21:11.143
Wait a minute, yeah.

1469
01:21:11.226 --> 01:21:12.560
Stop right there.

1470
01:21:12.643 --> 01:21:14.893
Senator, I'm the police chief.

1471
01:21:15.393 --> 01:21:16.851
I apologize, sir,

1472
01:21:17.518 --> 01:21:21.268
but I've received a tip
about a money laundering scheme


1473
01:21:21.351 --> 01:21:23.060
involving your painting.

1474
01:21:23.143 --> 01:21:24.893
Not that it means you're involved,

1475
01:21:24.976 --> 01:21:28.060
but there is evidence
that this painting is fake.


1476
01:21:28.810 --> 01:21:32.185
Deputy, I am a federal senator.

1477
01:21:32.268 --> 01:21:34.185
I have jurisdiction privileges.

1478
01:21:34.268 --> 01:21:35.768
-Really?
-Don't worry.


1479
01:21:35.851 --> 01:21:39.268
I will do everything I can
to clarify this situation.


1480
01:21:40.143 --> 01:21:41.310
Allow me.

1481
01:21:41.393 --> 01:21:43.768
He paid 50 thousand for the painting,

1482
01:21:43.851 --> 01:21:46.643
so he would get
three million for it legally.


1483
01:21:46.726 --> 01:21:51.143
Dirty money of unknown provenance
would get into his account legally.


1484
01:21:51.226 --> 01:21:55.935
Deputy, please,
you can speak to my lawyers.


1485
01:21:56.643 --> 01:21:59.393
-I trust the justice system.
-You won't arrest him?


1486
01:21:59.476 --> 01:22:01.601
-Arrest him! I'll do it, then.
-No!


1487
01:22:01.685 --> 01:22:04.351
-You're hurting me!
-I'll make a citizen's arrest!


1488
01:22:04.435 --> 01:22:06.143
-Arrest him, dude!
-Chief.


1489
01:22:06.226 --> 01:22:07.726
What's going on, Clóvis?

1490
01:22:07.810 --> 01:22:09.018
No, not her.

1491
01:22:09.101 --> 01:22:11.268
The Senator gets to walk, but she doesn't?

1492
01:22:11.351 --> 01:22:12.935
It is what it is.

1493
01:22:13.018 --> 01:22:17.268
You promised a money-laundering scheme
with fake paintings and a senator.


1494
01:22:17.351 --> 01:22:19.435
Senators are untouchable. Who's left?

1495
01:22:19.518 --> 01:22:21.476
The counterfeiter and the receiver.

1496
01:22:21.560 --> 01:22:25.351
Don't you know
that the weakest always goes to the wall?


1497
01:22:26.935 --> 01:22:29.560
-That wasn't the deal!
-I made a deal with you.


1498
01:22:29.643 --> 01:22:31.726
You brought her into it.

1499
01:22:31.810 --> 01:22:34.518
If you had told me the truth,
I would've helped.


1500
01:22:34.601 --> 01:22:36.435
I can't go back empty-handed.

1501
01:22:36.518 --> 01:22:39.768
I need to think about my promotion.

1502
01:22:39.851 --> 01:22:40.851
Right?

1503
01:22:42.310 --> 01:22:43.185
Take her.

1504
01:22:43.268 --> 01:22:45.310
She's a decent person.

1505
01:22:45.393 --> 01:22:47.101
She works. She has a trailer.

1506
01:22:47.185 --> 01:22:48.018
I do.

1507
01:22:48.101 --> 01:22:50.768
She is a fighter. 
I made her do it.

1508
01:22:50.851 --> 01:22:54.018
You said it was all
set and good to go.

1509
01:22:54.101 --> 01:22:56.226
I told you I'm a liability.

1510
01:23:00.060 --> 01:23:04.226
You can use it all against me,
but let her go.


1511
01:23:04.310 --> 01:23:07.810
Take me away from society and mankind…

1512
01:23:09.935 --> 01:23:12.268
but don't take the only person I love.

1513
01:23:16.601 --> 01:23:20.185
What is this, a
soap opera? What are you?

1514
01:23:21.185 --> 01:23:22.601
-Siblings.
-Siblings.


1515
01:23:47.726 --> 01:23:52.435
18 MONTHS LATER

1516
01:23:56.976 --> 01:23:59.226
<i>I served my time, all right?</i>

1517
01:23:59.310 --> 01:24:01.268
<i>The court, on the other hand,</i>

1518
01:24:01.351 --> 01:24:05.726
<i>sentenced me to eight years in prison,</i>
<i>but gradually reduced my sentence.</i>


1519
01:24:06.268 --> 01:24:10.851
<i>It was initially reduced for helping</i>
<i>to solve the crime I committed myself.</i>


1520
01:24:10.935 --> 01:24:12.935
<i>Then, it was reduced even more.</i>

1521
01:24:13.018 --> 01:24:15.101
<i>There were so many appeals,</i>

1522
01:24:15.185 --> 01:24:18.643
<i>that I think I was released</i>
<i>with some credits with the law.</i>


1523
01:24:19.435 --> 01:24:22.060
<i>And if you think my sentence was short,</i>

1524
01:24:22.143 --> 01:24:24.185
<i>even with all the evidence,</i>

1525
01:24:24.268 --> 01:24:26.476
<i>the Senator got away with everything.</i>

1526
01:24:34.893 --> 01:24:36.310
I can't believe it!

1527
01:24:41.435 --> 01:24:44.143
GET THE GRIFT

1528
01:24:53.226 --> 01:24:54.101
Here you go.

1529
